your journalist's credential?

605
00:29:06,460 --> 00:29:07,150
Yes.

606
00:29:07,750 --> 00:29:09,150
Who's going to grab that?

607
00:29:10,030 --> 00:29:10,930
Drop that idea.

608
00:29:11,030 --> 00:29:14,240
-I'm sure he won't grab that stuff.
-Journalism is a decent profession.

609
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,240
Come on, Baoying.

610
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:18,800
Baoying, come on.

611
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:21,680
Let me add one too.

612
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:23,310
What's that? Take it back!

613
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:24,500
Just for more fun.

614
00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:25,550
Baoying.

615
00:29:26,090 --> 00:29:27,760
He's getting started.

616
00:29:34,310 --> 00:29:35,510
Grab the journalist's credential.

617
00:29:35,510 --> 00:29:36,710
Go for the gold ingot.

618
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:38,220
Look at the gold ingot.

619
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:39,830
Grab one!

620
00:29:44,190 --> 00:29:45,240
He grabbed the police car!

621
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:46,570
What an good little boy.

622
00:29:46,830 --> 00:29:47,920
How very nice.

623
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,620
You're not drunk, are you?

624
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:40,620
No, I'm not.

625
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:43,960
You can really hold your liquor.

626
00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:49,410
Shall I ask?

627
00:30:50,750 --> 00:30:51,400
Okay.

628
00:30:53,310 --> 00:30:54,880
How long have you known Yan?

629
00:30:55,950 --> 00:30:58,350
Since high school.
We went to high school together.

630
00:30:58,350 --> 00:30:59,350
That early?

631
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:00,830
Yes.

632
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:03,780
When did you two start dating?

633
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:06,810
A-About six months ago.

634
00:31:07,070 --> 00:31:08,200
Six months already.

635
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:11,690
How many girlfriends
did you have before her?

636
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,110
Two.

637
00:31:14,150 --> 00:31:15,680
Why did you break up with them?

638
00:31:15,680 --> 00:31:17,000
One

639
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:18,480
went abroad.

640
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:20,230
The other one...

641
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:21,770
fought with me a lot.

642
00:31:22,070 --> 00:31:24,270
So you didn't do anything wrong, right?

643
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,880
You were not responsible for the breakups?

644
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:26,480
Well,

645
00:31:27,310 --> 00:31:28,110
not exactly.

646
00:31:28,110 --> 00:31:29,910
I-I'm sure I was partly to blame.

647
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:32,220
What did your ex-girlfriends

648
00:31:32,270 --> 00:31:33,600
mostly fight you about?

649
00:31:33,750 --> 00:31:35,250
They thought...

650
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:37,200
that I...

651
00:31:38,270 --> 00:31:39,860
couldn't make much money,

652
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:40,680
and...

653
00:31:41,070 --> 00:31:43,400
that I was never home
due to my job as a journalist.

654
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:44,240
I could rarely

655
00:31:44,550 --> 00:31:45,750
spend time with them.

656
00:31:45,750 --> 00:31:47,080
What do you think of Yan?

657
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:48,360
Yan?

658
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,370
She's great. Perfect, I'd say.

659
00:31:50,750 --> 00:31:51,880
What's so great about her?

660
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:52,790
Everything.

661
00:31:54,070 --> 00:31:55,470
Any specific qualities?

662
00:31:57,030 --> 00:31:57,560
She is...

663
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,160
lovable and pretty.

664
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:01,350
Outgoing and cheerful.

665
00:32:01,350 --> 00:32:04,010
-Generous...
-Stop throwing adjectives at us.

666
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,640
We want to hear something specific.

667
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:07,790
What are your plans for the future?

668
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:08,930
My plans...

669
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,210
are surely to

670
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:12,090
keep dating her.

671
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:14,000
No, no, no.

672
00:32:14,110 --> 00:32:16,000
That's not a proper way to put it.

673
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:16,550
I mean,

674
00:32:17,110 --> 00:32:19,480
I hope to take our relationship
to the next level soon.

675
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:20,410
Right? I will...

676
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:23,880
try building a stable home for Yan.

677
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:26,680
See,

678
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,790
this young fellow genuinely loves Yan.

679
00:32:28,790 --> 00:32:29,240
Yes.

680
00:32:29,550 --> 00:32:31,720
The purpose of this talk
is to let you know

681
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:33,310
that Yan has us two brothers,

682
00:32:33,310 --> 00:32:35,270
and that if you don't treat her right,

683
00:32:35,270 --> 00:32:36,460
we'll hunt you down.

684
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:37,920
T-That won't happen.

685
00:32:38,310 --> 00:32:39,400
That said, Yan also

686
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:41,040
has her flaws

687
00:32:41,070 --> 00:32:42,130
and shortcomings.

688
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:44,950
Sometimes when she gets hot-tempered,

689
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,600
she might be a bit mean to you.

690
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:48,200
Just be tolerant

691
00:32:48,480 --> 00:32:49,880
and process it yourself.

692
00:32:50,110 --> 00:32:51,070
We just hope

693
00:32:51,550 --> 00:32:52,400
to never hear

694
00:32:52,750 --> 00:32:53,750
that she's upset.

695
00:32:55,270 --> 00:32:56,550
What are you guys doing?

696
00:32:56,550 --> 00:32:57,720
I've been looking for you.

697
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:58,480
Who exactly do you mean?

698
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,940
You guys seem mysterious.

699
00:33:00,390 --> 00:33:01,320
All is fine.

700
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:03,750
Tianye and Feng
were just chatting with me.

701
00:33:04,110 --> 00:33:05,640
You bullied him again, didn't you?

702
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:06,570
No, they didn't.

703
00:33:07,790 --> 00:33:08,650
And you, silly,

704
00:33:08,830 --> 00:33:10,350
